  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nUser reported persistent iOS prompting for irrelevant browser extension setup. Manus clarified this is a platform-level UI behavior beyond assistant control and directed user to submit product feedback through proper channels.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser experiencing frustration with recurring iOS prompts for browser extension setup that isn't relevant to mobile usage\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nIdentified root cause as platform-level behavior, explained limitations of assistant control over system prompts, provided proper feedback channel\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [guidance] Product feedback direction — Clear instructions to submit feedback via help.manus.im for iOS-specific prompt suppression\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Direct user to proper product feedback channel rather than attempting workarounds\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Clear explanation of platform vs assistant limitations\n- Proper escalation path provided\nFailed / suboptimal:\n\n- Platform prompting logic not context-aware for mobile devices\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Browser extension prompts are system-level UI behaviors beyond assistant configuration\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- Platform-level UI behavior cannot be controlled by individual assistants\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Will platform team implement iOS-aware prompt logic?\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- User to submit product feedback for iOS prompt suppression feature request\n---\nUID: uLWouD3ZmuPhjnq5x9pv7x | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0091\n"
